1. d4 { [%clk 0:03:00] } 1... d6 { [%clk 0:03:00] } 2. e4 { [%clk 0:02:59] } 2... Nf6 { [%clk 0:02:59] } 3. Nc3 { [%clk 0:02:58] } 3... e5 { [%clk 0:02:59] } 4. Nf3 { [%clk 0:02:57] } 4... Nbd7 { [%clk 0:02:58] } 5. Bc4 { [%clk 0:02:56] } 5... h6 { [%clk 0:02:57] } 6. O-O { [%clk 0:02:54] } 6... Be7 { [%clk 0:02:57] } 7. Qe2 { [%clk 0:02:52] } 7... O-O { [%clk 0:02:55] } 8. Rd1 { [%clk 0:02:51] } 8... exd4 { [%clk 0:02:49] } 9. Nxd4 { [%clk 0:02:51] } 9... Re8?? { This is a losing mistake. I immediately recalled the famous Fischer - Reshevsky game, decided by the same combination. (True, it was a Sicilian Dragon, but who cares?) } { [%clk 0:02:47] } 10. Bxf7+! { [%clk 0:02:41] } 10... Kxf7 { [%clk 0:02:42] } 11. Ne6! { [%clk 0:02:41] } (11. Qc4+?? Kg6 12. Ne6 Ne5) 11... Kxe6 { [%clk 0:02:36] } 12. Qc4+ { [%clk 0:02:41] } 12... d5 { Here I spent quite some time deciding how to take on d5. Eventually I chose the best move. } { [%clk 0:02:32] } (12... Ke5 13. f4#) 13. Nxd5 { The mate is inevitable. } { [%clk 0:02:09] } (13. exd5+ Kf7 14. d6+ { wins as well, as black's queen is trapped after } 14... Kf8 15. dxc7! $18) (13. Rxd5? Nb6? (13... Bf8!! { The only move which allows black to stay alive. I missed it, but my intuition did not let me down this time. (True, 13.Nxd5 was not too difficult to calculate.) } 14. Rc5+ (14. Rf5+ Ke7 15. Nd5+ Nxd5 16. Qxd5 Ne5!! { The only move. } (16... Nf6? 17. Re5+ Be6 18. Qxe6#) 17. Qxe5+ Be6 18. Bf4 b6! { Black prevents 19.Qc5+ Kd7 20.Rd1, White is allegedly better after } 19. Bg3!! { (threatening 20.Bh4+ g5 21.Rxg5 hxg5 22.Bxg5+), but the position remains very messy. }) 14... Nd5!? (14... Ke7 15. Rxc7 b5! 16. Nxb5 Ba6 17. a4 { seems to favour white, but these computer lines have no connection to the game. }) 15. Rxd5 Kf6 { and the king escapes to h7 with unclear consequences. I do not trust black's position, but computer says that it hold. }) (13... Kf7 { saves the king but loses the queen after } 14. Rxd7+ $18 { . }) 14. Re5+!! Kxe5 15. f4+ Kd6 16. e5+! Kd7 17. e6+ Kd6 18. Nb5# { was the line which I liked most, but I was afraid that it could contain some flaws. (And it did, namely 13...Bf8!.) }) 13... Kf7 { [%clk 0:02:30] } (13... Nxd5 14. Qxd5+ Kf6 15. Qf5#) 14. Nf4+ { 1-0 Black resigns. } { [%clk 0:02:08] } 14... Kf8 15. Ng6# 1-0


