{ This is a game which I played on chess.com. I included it to this collection because of the brilliant mate. }
1. e4 c6 2. Nf3 d5 3. Nc3 Nf6 4. e5 Ne4 5. Ne2 Qb6 6. d4 h6 (6... e6 7. Ng3 c5 8. Bd3 Nxg3 9. fxg3 { I lost in this line more than once with black. The f7-pawn is vulnerable. }) 7. Ng3 (7. c3 e6 8. Nfg1 c5 9. f3 Ng5 10. h4 Nh7 11. f4 Nc6 12. Nf3 $16) 7... Nxg3 8. hxg3 Bf5 9. Nh4 (9. a4!? $14) 9... Bd7 10. c3 (10. Bd3 Qxd4?! 11. Nf3! Qb6 12. Ng5 Qc7 13. f4 g6 14. e6! Bxe6 15. Nxe6 fxe6 16. Bxg6+ Kd8 $14) 10... e6 11. Bd3 c5 12. O-O?! (12. dxc5!? Bxc5 13. Qe2 $14) 12... Nc6? (12... cxd4! 13. cxd4 Bb5 (13... Be7)) 13. dxc5! Bxc5 14. Qe2 (14. b4! Be7 15. Nf3 $16) 14... g5 15. Nf3 a5 16. Rb1 Na7? 17. b4! axb4 18. cxb4 Be7 19. Be3 Qd8 20. b5! Nc8 21. b6! $18 Bc6 22. Nd4 Bd7 23. f4 Nxb6 24. Nxe6 Bxe6 25. Bxb6 Qb8 26. f5 Bd7 27. e6 Bc6 28. exf7+ Kxf7 29. Qe6+ (29. Qh5+ Kf8 30. f6 $18) 29... Kf8 30. f6 Ba3 31. Bg6 Be8 32. f7 Bc6 33. Qe8+ Kg7 (33... Bxe8 34. fxe8=Q+) 34. Bd4+ Kxg6 { The following move was a bit hard to make with an automatic queen promotion set up, but I managed that. (You need to push the right key (and hold it, I guess) before promoting the pawn. Here it is Ctrl, there it is Alt. } 35. f8=N#! { FormerProdigy won by checkmate } { Other moves were also winning, but this leads to one of the nicest mates which I have ever delivered. } (35. f8=Q+?! Qxe8 36. Qf5+ Kh5 37. g4+ Kh4 38. Bf2#) 1-0


