{ A good game from a tournament where I performed poorly. }
1. e4 { [%clk 0:05:00] } 1... c5 { [%clk 0:05:00] } 2. c3 { [%clk 0:04:59] } 2... d5 { [%clk 0:04:59] } 3. exd5 { [%clk 0:04:58] } 3... Qxd5 { [%clk 0:04:59] } 4. d4 { [%clk 0:04:57] } 4... Nf6 { [%clk 0:04:58] } 5. Nf3 { [%clk 0:04:57] } 5... e6 { [%clk 0:04:58] } 6. Na3 { [%clk 0:04:53] } 6... Nc6 { [%clk 0:04:57] } 7. Nb5 { [%clk 0:04:50] } 7... Qd8 { [%clk 0:04:56] } 8. dxc5 { [%clk 0:04:49] } 8... Bxc5 { [%clk 0:04:52] } 9. Qxd8+ { [%clk 0:04:47] } 9... Kxd8 { [%clk 0:04:52] } 10. b4 { This should not bring white anything if black reacts accurately. } { [%clk 0:04:46] } 10... Bb6?! { [%clk 0:04:33] } (10... Be7! { is more accurate. }) 11. Nd6 { [%clk 0:04:44] } 11... Ke7 { [%clk 0:04:31] } 12. Nc4! { White will exchange his knight for the more active bishop. } { [%clk 0:04:43] } 12... Ne4 { [%clk 0:04:28] } 13. Nxb6 { [%clk 0:04:37] } 13... axb6 { [%clk 0:04:28] } 14. b5 { [%clk 0:04:25] } 14... Nb8 { [%clk 0:04:15] } 15. c4 { [%clk 0:04:12] } (15. a4!? Nd7 16. Ba3+ { would bring white initiative. }) 15... Rd8 { [%clk 0:04:08] } (15... Nd7!) 16. Be3 { [%clk 0:04:01] } 16... Nd7 { [%clk 0:04:03] } 17. Bd3 { [%clk 0:03:59] } 17... Nec5 { [%clk 0:03:56] } (17... Nd6!) 18. Bc2 { [%clk 0:03:58] } 18... Ra3 { [%clk 0:03:43] } 19. Ke2 { [%clk 0:03:53] } (19. O-O-O!? Rxa2 20. Kb1 Ra8 21. g4 { and white's activity weighs more than a pawn. }) 19... Rc3 { [%clk 0:03:41] } 20. Bb3 { [%clk 0:03:40] } 20... Nxb3 { [%clk 0:03:39] } 21. axb3 { [%clk 0:03:39] } 21... Rxb3 { [%clk 0:03:39] } 22. Nd2 { [%clk 0:03:23] } 22... Rb2?! { This is not the right way to sacrifice the exchange. } { [%clk 0:03:11] } (22... Rc3! { was stronger. After } 23. Bd4 (23. Rhc1 Rxc1 24. Rxc1 $15) 23... Rc2 24. Kd3 Rxd2+ 25. Kxd2 Nf6! { the play might transpose to the game. }) 23. Bd4? { Now everything will work well. } { [%clk 0:03:10] } (23. Rhb1! Rxb1 24. Nxb1! Nc5 25. Nc3 $14 { and black's bishop is pathetic. }) 23... Rxd2+! { [%clk 0:03:11] } 24. Kxd2 { [%clk 0:03:09] } 24... Nf6! { This move might have surprised white. The bishop is in a big danger. } { [%clk 0:03:11] } 25. Kc3! { [%clk 0:02:15] } (25. Kd3? e5 $19) (25. Ke3? Ng4+ 26. Ke4 f5+ 27. Kd3 e5 $19) 25... Ne4+ { [%clk 0:03:10] } 26. Kd3 { [%clk 0:02:12] } 26... Nxf2+ { [%clk 0:03:10] } 27. Ke3? { [%clk 0:02:11] } (27. Kc3! Ne4+ 28. Kd3 e5 29. Kxe4 Rxd4+ { This was my intention. } 30. Ke3 (30. Kxe5 Rxc4 { I believed that white's king would be mated there. In fact, } 31. Rhe1 Be6 32. Re4 Rc5+ 33. Kf4 Rxb5 $17 { is playable for white, though unpleasant. }) 30... f5 { Black is better, but the play goes on. } (30... Rxc4 31. Rhc1! { should be a draw. })) 27... Ng4+! { 0-1 White resigns. } { and white resigned. After 28.Ke4 f5+ 29.Kd3 e5 black wins the bishop and the game. } { [%clk 0:03:08] } (27... Nxh1? 28. Rxh1 $15 { would have given white great drawing chances. } (28. Bxb6!? $15)) 0-1


