1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 e6 3. Nc3 Bb4 4. e3 O-O 5. Bd3 d5 6. a3 Bxc3+ 7. bxc3 dxc4 8. Bxc4 c5 9. Ne2 Qc7 10. Bd3 b6 11. O-O Bb7 12. Ng3 Nc6 13. Bb2 Rfd8 14. f4 Rac8 15. Qe2 Qe7 16. Rad1 g6 17. h3 Ne8 18. Qf2 Nd6 19. e4 cxd4 20. cxd4 Na5 21. f5 exf5 22. d5 Nac4 23. Ba1 Ne5 24. exf5 Re8 25. Bb1 Qg5 26. fxg6 (26. Rde1 f6 27. Bxe5 fxe5 { [%cal Gf5g6] } 28. fxg6 hxg6 29. Ne4! Nxe4 30. Qf7+ { [%cal Gg8h8] } 30... Kh8 31. h4!) (26. Ne4! Nxe4 27. Bxe4 Ba6 28. fxg6! { is very bad for black. }) 26... hxg6 27. Rde1?! (27. Ne4! Nxe4 28. Bxe4 f5 29. Bb1 { is close to winning, black's king has been irreparably weakened. }) 27... Ba6 28. h4! Qxh4 29. Bxe5 Bxf1 30. Bxd6? (30. Bf6!! $16 Rxe1 31. Bxh4 Rxb1 32. Qf4! { with a strong attack. }) 30... Rxe1 31. Qxe1 Qd4+ (31... Bb5 32. Bxg6 Qd4+ 33. Kh2 Qh4+ $10) (31... Bd3 32. Bxd3 Qd4+ 33. Kh2 Qh4+! $10 (33... Qh8+! $10)) 32. Qf2 Qxf2+ 33. Kxf2 Bc4 { I went below 10 seconds around here and gained more time only at the very end of the game. } 34. Be4 f5 35. Bf3 $16 Kf7 36. Ke3 Rd8 37. Bc7 Rxd5 38. Bxd5+ Bxd5 39. Kf2 Ke6 40. Ne2 g5 41. Bb8 a6 42. Nd4+ Kf6 43. Bc7 b5 44. g3 f4 45. gxf4 gxf4 46. Bxf4 Bc4 47. Ke3 a5 48. Bc7 b4 49. a4 b3 50. Kd2 Bf7 51. Kc3 Be8 52. Nb5 Ke7 53. Kxb3 Kd7 54. Bxa5 $18 Kc6 55. Kb4 Bd7 56. Bd8 Kb7 57. Nd6+ Ka6 58. a5 Bc6 59. Kc5 Bf3 60. Bb6 Bg2 61. Kd4 Bc6 62. Ke5 Bd7 63. Kf6 Bc6 64. Ke7 Bd7 65. Ne4 Bc6 66. Nc5+ Kb5 67. Kd6 Bg2 68. Ne6 Ka6 69. Kc7 Bd5 70. Nc5+ Kb5 71. a6 Bf3 72. a7 Ba8 73. Kb8 Kxb6 { Here I premoved 74...Kc7, although I saw the knight checks with an easy win. } 74. Kxa8?? (74. Nd7+! Kc6 75. Kxa8 Kc7 76. Nb6 { with the decisive mutual zugzwang. }) (74. Na4+! Kc6 75. Kxa8 Kc7 76. Nb6) 74... Kc7 { Here white spent some time. In the meantime I premoved Kc7-c8-c7-c8... and repeated it once again a few seconds later, thus making 25 premoves in a row. All of them are completely forced and very obvious. (In the last 15 moves or so I was already above 10 seconds again, after a very long serious time trouble.) } 75. Nd3 Kc8 76. Nb4 Kc7 77. Nc2 Kc8 78. Ne3 Kc7 79. Nc4 Kc8 80. Nd2 Kc7 81. Nf3 Kc8 82. Nh4 Kc7 83. Ng6 Kc8 84. Nh8 Kc7 85. Nf7 Kc8 86. Ne5 Kc7 87. Nc6 Kc8 88. Nd8 Kc7 89. Nb7 Kc8 90. Nc5 Kc7 91. Ne4 Kc8 92. Nf6 Kc7 93. Nd5+ Kc8 94. Nb4 Kc7 95. Na6+ Kc8 96. Nb8 Kc7 97. Nd7 Kc8 98. Nc5 Kc7 { 1/2-1/2 The game is a draw. } 1/2-1/2


