{ This was a last-round game. I was on 8.5/10 and close to winning it, yet I blundered 58.b4+ and ended up in a difficult endgame, which I lost on time. (I would have most likely lost it anyway.) I claim that losing on time is a sort of a move, more concretely a sort of a blunder. }
1. Nf3 d5 2. b3 Nf6 3. Bb2 Bg4 4. e3 e6 5. h3 Bh5 6. d3 c5 7. g4 Bg6 8. Nh4 Nc6 9. Nd2 d4 10. Nxg6 hxg6 11. Bg2 Nd5 12. Qe2 Be7 13. O-O-O Ncb4 14. Bxd5 Qxd5 15. Kb1 O-O-O 16. f4 dxe3 17. Qxe3 Rh7 18. Rhf1 Nc6 19. Ne4 b6 20. Nc3 Qd7 21. Ne2 Bf6 22. Bxf6 gxf6 23. f5 exf5 24. gxf5 g5 25. Nc3 Rdh8 26. Ne4 Rxh3 27. Qf2 Qd4 28. Qxd4 Nxd4 29. Nxf6 Rf3 30. c3 Rxf1 31. Rxf1 Ne2 32. Ne4 Rh2 { After some ups and downs I achieved a winning position, but Hikaru played very resourcefully, showing his class. } 33. Nxg5 Nxc3+ 34. Kc1 Nxa2+ 35. Kb1 Nc3+ 36. Kc1 f6 37. Ne6 Ra2 38. Rf3 Kd7 39. Nf4 Ne2+ 40. Kb1 Nc3+ 41. Kc1 Ne2+ 42. Kb1 Rd2 43. Nd5 Nd4 44. Rh3 Nxf5 45. Nxf6+ Kc6 46. Ne4 Re2 47. Nc3 Re3 48. Rxe3 Nxe3 49. Ne2 Kb5 50. Kb2 Nd5 51. Ng3 Kb4 52. Ne4 Nf4 53. Kc2 Ne6 (53... b5 { followed by a knight transfer to d4 was winning. }) 54. Kb2 Nd4 55. Nc3! { a clever defense. } 55... a6 (55... b5! 56. Nd5+ Ka5) (55... Nxb3 56. Nd5+ Ka4 { [%cal Gd5c3] } 57. Nc3+ $10) 56. Nd5+ Ka5 57. Kc3 { White already holds, as black's king is poorly placed. } 57... b5? (57... Nb5+ 58. Kb2) 58. b4+! { White gains initiative. } 58... Ka4 59. bxc5 Nc6 60. Nb6+ Ka3 61. d4 b4+ 62. Kd3 b3 63. Kc3 b2? (63... Na5! 64. Nd5!! b2 65. Kc2 Nc6 66. Nc3 Nxd4+ 67. Kb1 Kb3 68. Nd1 $10) 64. Nc4+ Ka4 65. Nxb2+ Kb5 66. Nd3 { 1-0 White wins on time. } { I planned to play 66...Ne7 (if I remember correctly), but was too slow. } (66. Nc4! Ne7! $16 { might still hold in theory, but not in practice. }) 1-0


